## Error Handling Patterns

### Consistent Error Responses
```typescript
// Standardized error format
return NextResponse.json(
  { error: 'Descriptive error message' }, 
  { status: 400 }
)

// Error logging
console.error('Context for debugging:', error)
```

### Database Error Handling
```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('question_bank')
  .insert(questionData)

if (error) {
  console.error('Database error:', error)
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: error.message }, 
    { status: 500 }
  )
}
```

### Rate Limiting & Quotas
- OpenAI API calls are throttled
- Database queries are optimized with indexes
- LocalStorage usage is monitored

## Caching Strategies

### API Response Caching
- Units/lessons cached in context
- Question bank results cached with filters
- Usage statistics cached for performance

### Client-Side Storage
- LocalStorage for assignments/submissions
- SessionStorage for temporary data
- Context state for active session data

## Data Transformation Patterns

### Database to Context Mapping
```typescript
// Transform database format to context format
const transformedQuestions: QuestionBankItem[] = data.map((item: any) => ({
  id: item.id,
  question: item.question_data,        // JSONB to Question object
  unit: item.unit_id,
  lesson: item.lesson_id,
  topics: item.topics || [],
  difficulty: item.difficulty,
  usage_count: item.usage_count,
  created_at: item.created_at,
  updated_at: item.updated_at
}))
```

### Question Storage Optimization
```typescript
// Extract searchable fields from JSONB
if (updates.question_data) {
